cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically deep image matting. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a novel framework for learning to index, which involves training a neural network to predict indices for upsampling and pooling operations. This falls under the category of machine learning, which is covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of their approach on natural image matting, which involves segmenting an image into foreground and background regions. This falls under the category of graphics, which is covered by cs.GR (Computer Graphics). Finally, the paper presents results on the Composition-1k matting dataset, which is a benchmark for evaluating image matting algorithms. This falls under the category of multimedia, which is covered by cs.MM (Multimedia).
